<div class="expanded">
<h2 class="bac"><img class="pclose" src="../images/clear.gif">Our Business</h2>
<div>
<p class="bac">Chief Financial Office (CFO) partners with all business units, performing traditional finance and accounting functions, as well as strategic analysis. CFO helps execute strategic goals, drive disciplined growth, and enhance operational efficiencies at every level. CFO is also responsible for the firm&#39;s market and credit risk management, treasury, financial and regulatory reporting and controls, corporate and strategic planning, internal audit, and tax policy, as well as regulatory supervision on a global basis.</p>
</div></div>

<div class="expand">
<h2 class="bac"><img class="popen" src="../images/clear.gif">Overview</h2>
<div>
<p class="bac">Chief Financial Office (CFO) Fulltime Analyst Program is designed to provide candidates with an opportunity to work with experienced finance professionals and prepare for a career in the bank&#39;s finance division.</p>
<h3 class="bac">Placement</h3 >
<p class="bac">CFO Analysts are placed directly with a specific team in Singapore, Hong Kong or Japan.</p>
<h3 class="bac">Responsibilities</h3>
<ul class="bac">
	<li>Exposure to management forecasting and detailed cost interpretation and analysis</li>
	<li>Exposure to statutory accounting, corporate and regulatory reporting</li>
	<li>Modify current reporting systems and recommending procedures to improve the productivity and efficiency of the team</li>
	<li>Exposure to project activities including business case development, financial modeling/ projection, analysis of financials and Finance requirements</li>
	<li>Exposure to project management activities including task tracking   &amp;amp; reporting, cost tracking  &amp; reporting, project coordination</li>
	<li>Assist CFO with management of Finance department activities including tracking and reporting key Finance initiatives, communication with CFO direct reports, ad hoc projects/reports, etc.</li>
	<li>Exposure to and helping CFO with business strategy/plan presentations</li>
</ul>
</div></div>

<div class="expand">
<h2 class="bac"><img class="popen" src="../images/clear.gif">Qualifications</h2>
<div>
<h3 class="bac">Education</h3>
<ul class="bac">
	<li>Final year undergraduate/master student, graduating in 2010</li>
	<li>Good academic achievement</li>
	<li>Major in accounting or finance, or a related area</li>
</ul>
<h3 class="bac">Experience</h3>
<ul class="bac">
	<li>A track record of superior performance in extracurricular and professional activities </li>
	<li>Prior relevant internship experience advantageous</li>
</ul>
<h3 class="bac">Skills and abilities</h3>
<ul class="bac">
	<li>Knowledge of basic accounting and finance principles and the ability to apply them to work situations</li>
	<li>Strong quantitative and analytical skills</li>
	<li>Creative thinking and problem-solving skills</li>
	<li>Strong presentation and interpersonal skills </li>
	<li>Ability to produce high quality work in a demanding environment</li>
	<li>Ability to work independently while functioning as part of a team </li>
	<li>Project management skills and financial industry knowledge</li>
</ul>
<h3 class="bac">Personal traits</h3>
<ul class="bac">
	<li>Commitment to a career in the financial services industry</li>
	<li>High degree of professionalism and integrity</li>
	<li>High degree of initiative and motivation</li>
	<li>Quick learner and interest in taking on new responsibilities</li>
	<li>Strong attention to detail</li>
	<li>Ability to work well with others</li>
	<li>Client-focused </li>
	<li>Results-oriented</li>
</ul>
</div></div>

<div class="expand">
<h2 class="bac"><img class="popen" src="../images/clear.gif">Training</h2>
<div>
<p class="bac nobr">The Fulltime Analyst Program consists of the following developmental activities:</p>
<ul class="bac">
	<li>Access to pre-work via an online e-learning portal covering foundation topics</li>
	<li>Introductory and ongoing training program (including on the job and/or classroom training) </li>
	<li>An overview of the financial markets and essential business skills</li>
	<li>Business critical assignments</li>
	<li>Exposure to senior leadership teams</li>
	<li>Networking and social events</li>
	<li>Buddy and mentorship program</li>
</ul>
</div></div>

